1/ create virtual environment
>virtualenv py_websocket_tut_1_venv

2/ activate the virtual enviornment
>source <name_of_env>/bin/activate

3/ to deactivate:
>deactivate

4/ create a build enviornment in sublime:
	a. tools-> build system -> New Build System
	give it a descriptive name:
	websocket-tut1-virtualenv

	b. open the build system by double clicking on it:
	/users/ezouras/Library/Application Support/Sublime Text 3/Packages/User/<name of build system>

	c. add the following:
	{
	    "cmd": ["/Users/ezouras/Documents/EvieSoftware/Angular/websockets/py_websocket_tut_1_venv/bin/python", "$file"],
	    "selector": "source.python",
	    "file_regex": "^\\s*File \"(...*?)\", line ([0-9]*)"
	}

	where "/Users/ezouras/Documents/EvieSoftware/Angular/websockets/py_websocket_tut_1_venv/bin/python"
	is based on your virutal environment. 

	setup.py

	